 {"id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3","title":"[Phase 5][Support] Fix active compile blockers in openai provider and interactive agent surfaces","description":"Non-overlapping support slice under bd-3ar8v.6.6 scoped to src/providers/openai.rs and src/interactive/agent.rs only: resolve currently active compile failures reported by all-target check/clippy (excluding src/rpc.rs, reserved by CyanPond) to reduce gate blockers.","notes":"Deferred: current reproducible blockers are Send/HRTB spawn regressions in src/interactive/agent.rs (lines ~788 and ~1069) with matching pattern in src/rpc.rs currently held by CyanPond; released reservations, no code edits made.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PearlSnow","created_at":"2026-02-16T20:59:14.106580313Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-17T00:09:27.132355195Z","closed_at":"2026-02-17T00:09:27.132249879Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["compile","perf-3x","phase-5","stability","support"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-16T20:59:14.106580313Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.1","title":"[Phase 5][Support] Fix interactive runtime_handle.spawn Send/FnOnce bound regressions in agent surface","description":"Non-overlapping support slice under bd-3ar8v.6.6.3 scoped to src/interactive/agent.rs only: resolve runtime_handle.spawn async closure bound regressions (FnOnce/Send not general enough) in run_prompt_with_retry call paths so focused perf_regression test builds can proceed.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GreenBadger","created_at":"2026-02-16T21:03:08.867946825Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T21:12:00.994854273Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T21:12:00.994811093Z","close_reason":"Completed (interactive spawn lock lifetimes fixed with OwnedMutexGuard; focused rch target builds/tests pass)","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-16T21:03:08.867946825Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":1872,"issue_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Started. Reserved src/interactive/agent.rs exclusively (reason: bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.1). Targeting runtime_handle.spawn run_prompt_with_retry closure bound regressions (FnOnce/Send not general enough) while keeping behavior unchanged and avoiding src/rpc.rs surface owned by CyanPond.","created_at":"2026-02-16T21:03:32Z"},{"id":1873,"issue_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Implemented in src/interactive/agent.rs: switched spawned-path locks from borrowed guard API to asupersync::sync::OwnedMutexGuard::lock(Arc::clone(...), &cx) for both agent/session in both submit_content_with_display and submit_message_with_dispatch flows. This removes non-Send borrow lifetimes from the spawned futures. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/interactive/agent.rs passed; focused rch run succeeded once: cargo test --test perf_regression binary_size_candidate_ -- --nocapture => 7 passed, 0 failed. A later rerun hit remote artifact/fs races (No such file/dir during copy and jemalloc build dir writes), treated as infrastructure noise rather than code regression.","created_at":"2026-02-16T21:11:42Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.2","title":"[Phase 5][Support] Use owned ToolCall futures in execute_tool_calls to satisfy Send bounds","description":"Non-overlapping compile-unblock slice under bd-3ar8v.6.6.3 scoped to src/agent.rs only: switch execute_tool_calls concurrent map to owned ToolCall + cloned on_event futures (via execute_tool_owned) to remove borrowed future lifetime generalization that currently trips runtime_handle.spawn Send/FnOnce checks in rpc/interactive surfaces.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GreenBadger","created_at":"2026-02-16T21:07:20.189738016Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T21:12:14.014068656Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T21:12:14.014039461Z","close_reason":"Superseded/aborted in this lane (agent.rs overlap active; interactive-side fix resolved targeted compile path)","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-16T21:07:20.189738016Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":1874,"issue_id":"bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Stand-down: detected active overlap on src/agent.rs (holder: RusticDesert) and did not edit that file. After implementing bd-3ar8v.6.6.3.1 interactive-side OwnedMutexGuard lock conversion, focused rch perf_regression target compiled/ran successfully, so this speculative agent.rs slice is currently unnecessary in my lane.","created_at":"2026-02-16T21:12:08Z"}]}
